        print()  # Print a blank line between cases
    for shirt in case:
        print(f'{shirt[0]} {shirt[1]} {shirt[2]}')
```

This approach uses tuple sorting with a custom key, which is more idiomatic in Python and avoids the complexity of manually implementing sorting algorithms.

